\section{System Architecture}
% -------------------------------------------------------

\subsection{Architecture Overview}
The system is a full-stack web application built on Django 4.2 (Python 3.11) with MySQL 8.0, organized into five layers. The \textbf{Presentation Layer} (Bootstrap 5.3, vanilla JavaScript) takes care of displaying questions, capturing answers, and running a 20-minute countdown timer. It also enforces a fullscreen gate via the browser Fullscreen API and uses \texttt{navigator.sendBeacon} to auto-submit the test if the tab is closed. The \textbf{Controller Layer} (Django views) coordinates the test lifecycle, runs the synchronous rule-based difficulty fallback, and spawns asynchronous agent threads. The \textbf{AI/Agent Pipeline Layer} runs the CrewAI pipeline (MCQ Evaluator Agent $\rightarrow$ Difficulty Predictor Agent $\rightarrow$ Adaptive MCQ Overseer Agent) in a background daemon thread that talks to Gemini 2.5 Flash through CrewAI's \texttt{LLM} interface. The \textbf{Question Generation Layer} calls Gemini through the \texttt{google-generativeai} SDK to produce MCQs on the fly, following a strict JSON schema. The \textbf{Data Layer} is backed by three MySQL models: \texttt{StudentTestResult}, \texttt{QuestionPerformance}, and \texttt{AdaptiveLearningHistory}.

